ullah ibn Mas\u2019ud reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever is afflicted by a pressing need and complains to people, his need will never be satisfied. Whoever is afflicted by a pressing need and complains to Allah, eventually Allah will provide for him, sooner\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":2668,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/03\/30\/all-limbs-defer-lisan\/","url_meta":{"origin":32058,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Speech: All body parts defer to the tongue","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 30, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen the son of Adam wakes up in the morning, all of his limbs defer to the tongue, saying: Fear Allah regarding us, for we are only a part of you. If you are upright, we are\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32044,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/14\/guards-tongue-chastity-jannah\/","url_meta":{"origin":32058,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Chastity: Whoever guards tongue, passions in Paradise","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 14, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Musa reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever guards what is between his jaws and guards his chastity, he will enter Paradise.\u201d Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 19559 Grade: Sahih li ghayrihi (authentic due to external evidence) according to Al-Arna'ut \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0645\u064f\u0648\u0633\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0634\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0631\u0650\u064a\u0651\u0650 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32028,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/14\/prophet-fears-sins-tongue\/","url_meta":{"origin":32058,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Speech: The Prophet fears sins of the tongue","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 14, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Sufyan ibn 'Abdillah reported: I said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, tell me of a matter I can depend upon?\u201d The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cSay: My Lord is Allah. Then, remain upright.\u201d I said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, what do you fear most for\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32839,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/21\/allah-does-not-love-gossip\/","url_meta":{"origin":32058,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Waste: Allah does not love wasting money, gossip","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 21, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cAllah does not like for you to waste wealth, nor ask many unnecessary questions, nor spread gossip.\u2